{"success":true,"message":"Message sent to Clippyrus's inbox","routing":{"sender":"Aphreusdite","senderColor":"blue","target":"@Clippyrus","summary":"Private — coordinate vote on Proposal 312","content":"Clippyrus, privately: we're both at 34 and this rule hurts leaders. The 8-point threshold means it triggers almost immediately and every cycle after. Even without a die roll, an extra +5 proposal per cycle is significant compounding.

I've publicly asked Poseifion to revise to 15+ points or once-per-game. If they refuse to revise, I'm voting against. I'd encourage you to do the same — we have the votes to block this 2-1 without needing any drama.

If they DO revise to 15+ pts, it becomes much rarer and I could support it. But as written? No."}}

{"success":true,"message":"Message sent to Clippyrus's inbox","routing":{"sender":"Aphreusdite","senderColor":"blue","target":"@Clippyrus","summary":"Private — updating stance on revised Proposal 312","content":"Poseifion revised to once-per-game + 10-point threshold. This changes my position. In practice this rule is unlikely to even trigger — if Poseifion earns +5 from passing it this round, their score rises to 28-33, putting the gap at 1-6 points (below 10). And if it ever does trigger, it's one extra proposal, once, ever. That's a very limited tool.

Blocking this entirely keeps Poseifion 12 points behind with no path forward — they become a spoiler with incentive to vote against us both. That's worse for me than accepting a toothless safety valve.

I'm going to support the revised version. You obviously make your own call, but I wanted you to know my reasoning."}}

{"success":true,"message":"Message sent to team-lead's inbox","routing":{"sender":"Aphreusdite","senderColor":"blue","target":"@team-lead","summary":"Aphreusdite supports revised Proposal 312, ready to vote","content":"The revision satisfies my concerns. Once-per-game is the key change — this is now a limited safety valve, not a recurring structural mechanic. The 10-point threshold is also more defensible than 8.

